### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

core

### Is this a regression?

No

### Description

If you call `detectChanges()` on `ChangeDetectorRef` or `tick()` on `ApplicationRef` outside of an angular zone then the view is updated correctly but click handlers are still not in the angular zone.

But this depend on whether the element with the `(click)` event handles is inside or outside of a `ngFor` loop.

```typescript
this.zone.runOutsideAngular(() => {
  setInterval(() => {
    this.items = Array(1).fill(`click me`);
    this.changeDetection.detectChanges();
  }, 500);
});

clickButton() {
  console.log(`click event in NgZone: ${NgZone.isInAngularZone()}`);
}

/*
<button *ngFor="let item of items" (click)="clickButton()">
  {{ item }}
</button>
-> click event in NgZone: false


<button (click)="clickButton()">{{ items[0] }}</button>
-> click event in NgZone: true
*/
```




